replies.bodyText:
Just ran some experiments to remove T,
changes
  <T> T apply(@NonNull U annotation, @Nullable T fieldDecodedResult, @NonNull Class<T> type);

to
  Object apply(@NonNull U annotation, @Nullable Object fieldDecodedResult, @NonNull Class<?> type);

which allows us to write lambda like the following:
  private final static AnnotatedFieldHandler<Default> DEFAULT_HANDLER =
          (an, res, type) -> {
    if (res == null) {
      if (type.equals(String.class)) {
        return an.value();
      }
    }
    return res;
  };

But, we still not be able to directly register AnnotatedFieldHandler as lambda, since It still needs the info about the type of the Annotation, in that case, it's the U in above apply method.
any idea of fully supporting lambda?

